<p>What you do in the game moves the story forward. Although you‚Äôre in fact communicating with software, SPYSCAPE wants it to feel like you‚Äôre communicating with real people. But the question was how to do this at scale?
The game already used a large branching script about the length of a typical novel. This allows the characters to react to the choices that players make in the game, which begins to establish the feeling of reality.</p>

